oai_dc:dc.dc:title: West view of Cragfont
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Color photograph of the exterior of Cragfont, the home of General James Winchester. A wooden fence is in the foreground and the house is visible in the distance. Features a divided back, narrative, and handwritten correspondence on reverse. Note: this is an additional copy of this postcard and is the same as 49152.
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Commercial appeal (Memphis, Tenn.)
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Houses; Fences; Historic buildings; Trees
